      • DecisionModel

        public DecisionModel​(java.lang.String modelName)
        It's an equivalent of DecisionModel(modelName, defaultTrackURL, defaultTrackApiKey) We suggest to have the defaultTrackURL/defaultTrackApiKey set on startup before creating any DecisionModel instances.
        Parameters:
        modelName - Length of modelName must be in range [1, 64]; Only alphanumeric characters([a-zA-Z0-9]), '-', '.' and '_' are allowed in the modelName and the first character must be an alphanumeric one.

      • DecisionModel

        public DecisionModel​(java.lang.String modelName,
                     java.lang.String trackURL,
                     java.lang.String trackApiKey)
        Parameters:
        modelName - Length of modelName must be in range [1, 64]; Only alphanumeric characters([a-zA-Z0-9]), '-', '.' and '_' are allowed in the modelName and the first character must be an alphanumeric one.
        trackURL - url for tracking decisions. If trackURL is null, no decisions would be tracked. If trackURL is not a valid URL, an exception would be thrown.
        trackApiKey - will be attached to the header fields of all the post request for tracking
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if an invalid modelName or an invalid trackURL

      • load

        public DecisionModel load​(java.net.URL modelUrl)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Load a model synchronously. Calling this method would block the current thread, so please try not do it in the UI thread.
        Parameters:
        modelUrl - A url that can be a local file path, a remote http url that points to a model file, or a bundled asset. Urls that ends with '.gz' are considered gzip compressed, and will be handled appropriately. Bundled model asset urls appears a bit different. Suppose that you have a bundled model file in folder "assets/models/my_model.xgb.gz", then modelUrl should be new URL("file:///android_asset/models/my_model.xgb").
        Returns:
        Returns self.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown if the model failed to load.

      • loadAsync

        @Deprecated
public void loadAsync​(java.net.URL modelUrl,
                      DecisionModel.LoadListener listener)
        Deprecated.
        The callback method signature will likely have to change for multiple URLs
        Notice that it's not recommended to call this method directly in an Android Activity as it may cause leaks. Before we add a cancel method to allow aborting downloading tasks, you may have to call loadAsync() in something like a Singleton class.
        Parameters:
        modelUrl - A url that can be a local file path, a remote http url that points to a model file, or a bundled asset. Urls that ends with '.gz' are considered gzip compressed, and will be handled appropriately. Bundled model asset urls appears a bit different. Suppose that you have a bundled model file in folder "assets/models/my_model.xgb.gz", then modelUrl should be new URL("file:///android_asset/models/my_model.xgb").
        listener - The callback that will run when the model is loaded.

      • fullFactorialVariants

        public java.util.List<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object>> fullFactorialVariants​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> variantMap)
        An example here might be more expressive: fullFactorialVariants({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3, 5]}) returns [ {"style":"bold", "size":3}, {"style":"italic", "size":3}, {"style":"bold", "size":5}, {"style":"italic", "size":5}, ]
        Parameters:
        variantMap - The values of the variant map are expected to be lists of any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity. If they are not lists, they are automatically wrapped as a list containing a single item. So fullFactorialVariants({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":3}) is equivalent to fullFactorialVariants({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3]})
        Returns:
        Returns the full factorial combinations of key and values specified by the input variant map.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if variantMap is nil or empty; Thrown if variantMap values are all empty lists.

      • optimize

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object> optimize​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> variantMap)
        This method is a short hand of chooseMultivariate(variants).get().
        Parameters:

If they are not lists, they are automatically wrapped as a list containing a single item. So optimize({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":3}) is equivalent to optimize({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3]})

      • chooseMultivariate

        @Deprecated
public Decision<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?>> chooseMultivariate​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> variants)
        Deprecated.
        Remove in 8.0. Use decide(fullFactorialVariants(Map))
        This method is an alternative of chooseFrom(). An example here might be more expressive: optimize({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3, 5]}) is equivalent to chooseFrom([ {"style":"bold", "size":3}, {"style":"italic", "size":3}, {"style":"bold", "size":5}, {"style":"italic", "size":5}, ])
        Parameters:
        variants - Variants can be any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity like chooseFrom(). The value of the dictionary is expected to be a list. If not, it would be automatically wrapped as a list containing a single item. So chooseMultivariate({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":3}) is equivalent to chooseMultivariate({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3]})
        Returns:
        An IMPDecision object.

      • scoreInternal

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Double> scoreInternal​(java.util.List<?> variants,
                                                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> givens)
        If this method is called before the model is loaded, or errors occurred while loading the model file, a randomly generated list of descending Gaussian scores is returned.
        Parameters:
        variants - Variants can be any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity, including nested maps, arrays, strings, numbers, nulls, and booleans.
        givens - Additional context info that will be used with each of the variants to calculate the score, including the givens passed in through DecisionModel.given(givens) and the givens provided by the AppGivensProvider or other custom GivensProvider.
        Returns:
        scores of the variants
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if variants is null or empty

      • addReward

        public void addReward​(double reward)
        This method should only be called on Android platform. Adds the reward value to the most recent Decision for this model name for this installation. The most recent Decision can be from a different DecisionModel instance or a previous session as long as they have the same model name. If no previous Decision is found, the reward will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        reward - the reward to add. Must not be NaN, or Infinity.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if `reward` is NaN or Infinity
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - Thrown if trackURL is null, or called on non-Android platform.

      • addReward

        public void addReward​(double reward,
                      java.lang.String decisionId)
        Add reward for the provided decisionId
        Parameters:
        reward - reward for the decision.
        decisionId - unique id of a decision.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if decisionId is null or empty; Thrown if reward is NaN or Infinity.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - Thrown if trackURL is null. Adds the reward to a specific decision
